{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_63","type":"agent_message","text":"The provenance is threaded correctly when a push succeeds, and legacy rows remain compatible. However, one major stale-provenance defect makes the lane fail review.\n\nChecks:\n\n- `CommitInfo.oid` is captured, persisted to `.hf_push.json`, and propagated into watcher/gate journal and registry metadata.\n- Legacy journal rows remain valid; `should_retrain` ignores journal provenance and retrains when incumbent metadata lacks `dataset_digest`.\n- Push-related tests mock `DatasetDict.push_to_hub`, `HfApi.upload_file`, or the export boundary. No live pushes occur.\n\nTest result:\n\n```text\n665 passed, 36 warnings in 14.44s\n```\n\nNo failing tests.\n\nVERDICT: FAIL\n\n- **Major** — [/Users/yasyf/Code/cc-steer-c5/cc_steer/export.py:940](/Users/yasyf/Code/cc-steer-c5/cc_steer/export.py:940): A local-only or failed-push export leaves an existing `.hf_push.json` untouched, causing new journal and registry rows to claim a stale Hugging Face revision. Failure scenario: dataset A is pushed and records `sha-A`; the corpus changes and dataset B is exported into the same directory with `push_to=None`, or a push fails and the pipeline falls back locally; B’s parquet files replace A’s, but `hf_revision()` still returns `sha-A`, so retraining records B’s digest against A’s revision."}}
